
			
									<h5>Release Date: 9 November 2020</h5>
				
									Neo4j 4.1.4 is a maintenance release with many important improvements and fixes.
<h3>Highlights</h3>

<ul>
   <li>Special handling of unrelated SSL policies in the backup command</li>
   <li>Allow transactions with both read queries and schema commands</li>
   <li>Add procedure to set default database in cluster</li>
   <li>Fixed bug where clusters could get stuck bootstrapping in the event of network issues or instance restarts.</li>
   <li>Browser: Do not store connection passwords in local storage before receiving neo4j config</li>
</ul>
  

<h3>Detailed Changes and Docs</h3>
For the complete list of all changes, please see <a href="https://github.com/neo4j/neo4j/wiki/Neo4j-4.1-changelog" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">the changelog</a>.
Look for 4.1 Operations manual <a href="https://neo4j.com/docs/operations-manual/4.1/">here</a>.				
					